OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFashion giant Saint Laurent
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fto ban use of fur in 2022  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%title3
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The luxury French fashion brand Saint  
OL,6, Laurent will stop designing clothes    
OL,7, using fur from next year, its parent   
OL,8, company Kering has said.               
OL,10,FAnother Kering brand, Brioni, would    
OL,11,Falso be fur-free by the autumn 2022    
OL,12,Fcollections, the firm said.            
OL,14,FKering CEO Francois-Henri Pinault said 
OL,15,Fthe world "has changed".               
OL,17,FPeople for the Ethical Treatment of    
OL,18,FAnimals (Peta) welcomed the move after 
OL,19,Fwhat it called a "decades-long" push to
OL,20,Fget Kering to ban the use of fur.      
